	     Gauteng - A 51-year-old man is believed to have committed suicide earlier on Saturday after having jumped from the 23 floor of the Michelangelo Towers in Sandton on Saturday morning.  Police spokesperson, Captain Kay Makhubele confirmed the incident, saying the man had died instantly after plummeting to the ground shortly after 11:00 on Saturday.  According to one eye witness, Khutali, who took to twitter, the man had first hit a glass awning, before hitting into the back of a motor vehicle. Just saw some1 drop 4rm da Michael Angelo TowersSmashed da glas shade cover thing outside the entrance carried it &Smashed onto some1's Honda Civic/Corolla, broke the back window "The motive behind the incident is unknown and the police are investigating," Makhubele said.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  